overview: The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application,
  providing a comprehensive specification and SOW. The assistant performed a
  detailed analysis, identifying key functional areas that were well-implemented
  and several critical gaps. A structured plan was then generated, prioritizing
  the missing features. The assistant began implementing this plan by first
  adding a 1-10 tiredness severity scale to the questionnaire, including a
  safety warning for high scores in both the interactive form and the generated
  reports. Subsequently, the assistant implemented detection logic for Comorbid
  Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA), ensuring it was accurately reflected in the
  report sections and PDF output with specific recommendations. The approach
  involved systematic updates to data models, validation, UI components, and
  report generation logic.
